<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" CalDefCategory="Audio" Description="This file contains calibrations for the SinkLevelController defined in GIS-604 which computes the sink levels for both an internally amplified CSM or Low Radio as well as for the remote Amplifier via the GIS-633 spec over CAN.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>15</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>03JAN2014</Date>
    <Description>Version 2 was released along with GIS-604 V1.1 and contains numerous additions and update corrections as part of the final cleanup of GIS-604.  See change records on specific calibrations for details.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>28JAN2014</Date>
    <Description>Deleted RearChimeBoostLevel calibration.  This cal didn't belong in SinkLevelControls.caldef and is instead being reborn as K_REAR_CHIME_BOOST in the gis631 chime amp/interface caldef instead.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Added Usage on LOW, MID, and HIGH</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>10/31/2014</Date>
    <Description>Addition of &quot;STREAM_NATIVE_HFM_WB&quot; to SourceOffsetCCalibrationMap calID file.  This is in response to Harman Assembla ticket #1223.  </Description>
    <Author>Dominic Colella</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>2/8/2015</Date>
    <Description>Switched the max and min values for the MaxMixPromptLevel Cal to correct the issue with the min and max values being reversed for this Cal after confirming this with Dominic Colella.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>3/4/2016</Date>
    <Description>Updated PROMPT level in MinimumActivationVolumeMap based on tuning results. Upates to volume groups MUSIC, AUDIO_CUE, and RING to lower default levels for better customer experience.</Description>
    <Author>Dominic Colella</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>5/31/2016</Date>
    <Description>MidChimeBoostLevel - Default value changed from 6 to 3 dB due to complains on chime volume loudness.  MidChimeBoostStepThreshold - Default value changed from step 15 to 25.  HighChimeBoostLevel - Default value changed from 9 to 6 dB due to complains on chime volume loudness.  HighChimeBoostStepThreshold - Default value changed from step 40 to 47.  SeparationGain - Updated Separation Gain curve based on integration testing and MY17 cal override submitted for production.  </Description>
    <Author>Dominic Colella</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>6/24/2016</Date>
    <Description>In the SourceOffsetCalibrationMap calibration made the following audio stream default value updates based on feedback from MY17 vehicle testing: STREAM_MUSIC - Default value changed from 0 to 3 dB, 14.STREAM_NATIVE_AM_TUNER - Default value changed from 0 to 3 dB, STREAM_NATIVE_SDARS_TUNER - Default value changed from 0 to 7 dB, STREAM_NATIVE_IPOD - Default value changed from 0 to 5 dB, STREAM_NATIVE_DTCP_CALL - Default value changed from 5 to 16 dB, STREAM_VOICE_CALL - Default value changed from 0 to 24 dB, STREAM_NATIVE_MEDIA_PLAYER - Default value changed from 0 to 4 dB, STREAM_NATIVE_BLUETOOTH_AUDIO - Default value changed from 0 to 4 dB,and STREAM_NATIVE_LVM_STEREO_AUDIO  - Default value changed from 0 to 20 dB.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>1/20/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the SinkLevelControlCals.caldef file, made the following default value updates based on feedback and vehicle verification testing done for MY17 Info3: Updated the VOL_GROUP_VOICE_CALL calibration from a value of 28 to 18 within the MinimumActivationVolumeMap EnumInteger Map calibration.  Also, updated Updated the default value of the MinAudibleFeedbackLevel calibration from -50 to -22 dB.  And, Updated the default value of the AudibleFeedbackBoostLevel calibration from 6 to 20.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>2/13/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the SinkLevelControlCals.caldef file, made the following default value update based on feedback and vehicle verification testing done for MY17 Info3: Updated the default value of the  VOL_GROUP_EMERGENCY_PHONE calibration from a value of 28 to 26 within the MinimumVolumeMap EnumInteger Map calibration.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough </Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>2017-Jun-22</Date>
    <Description>As per CR 1371572 revising max value from 15 to 25 for SCVChimeBoostTable Array</Description>
    <Author>Kiran Soni</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Added GEM usage to all of the calibrations in the SinkLevelControlCals.caldef . Since all of these calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>9/11/2018</Date>
    <Description>CR1261915 - Added new stream type STREAM_NATIVE_PROJ_ALT_AUDIO  in SourceOffsetCalibrationMap</Description>
    <Author>Christine Marzan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>6/13/2019</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#2060763 AOSP transition, in MY22 GIS-646 Cal DB V6.0.3 for MinimumVolumeMap, MaximumVolumeMap, MinimumActivationVolumeMap, VolumeGroupInitialDefaultsMap, SourceOffsetCalibrationMap - uncheck MID/HIGH, VCU. Replacement MID/HIGH, VCU calibrations can be found in AOSPSinkLevelControl.caldef &amp; AOSPSinkLevelControlEnum.enumdef. Per CR# 2303227, in MY22 GIS-646 Cal DB V6.0.3 deprecating the following cals: SCVEnabled, SCVVolumeCompensationFactorStepTable, SCVVehicleSpeedUpdateDelta, SCVVolumeCompensationFactorLevelScaleTable, SCVLevelScaleTable, SCVVolumeBoostTable, SCVVolumeBoostSpeedTable, SCVBassBoostTable, SCVBassBoostSpeedTable, and SCVDefaultMenuSelection. These cals will not be supported.</Description>
    <Author>Christine Marzan</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
